This paper focuses on the relationship between code clones and faults, which is a common issue in software engineering (cs.SE). The study specifically looks at Java systems, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL). The methodology involves analyzing issue tracking and version control, which is related to software development (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the use of tool support for developers, which could fall under computer security (cs.CR) or machine learning (cs.LG) if the tool support involves automated detection or prediction.
